to the editor the announcement that a 21 year old murder case had been solved because of a dna match news article march 13 is the latest and perhaps best indication as to why laws expanding the use of these genetic fingerprints work certainly any improper use of dna samples should be rigorously punished however the dna sample collected for law enforcement purposes is referred to as junk dna because it does not contain sufficient genetic markers to provide any information about the individual beyond identification and just as dna can be used to convict it can likewise be used to acquit dna can be to law enforcement in this century what fingerprinting was in the last gov george e pataki 's proposal to expand the list of crimes for which dna samples can be taken deserves support mark green public advocate new york march 14 2000

